				<div class="col-md-6 col-lg-6">
					<p style="text-align:justify">
						<br> The adjacent graph has been created based on data created by the <strong>Australian Bureau of Statistics in 2016</strong>. It shows the number of homeless men and women living in different accommodations. From the adjacent graph, it can be clearly derived that the ‘Severely Crowded Dwellings’ which usually includes a house with 3 rooms are mostly accommodated by men than women. On the contrary, women have seemed to receive a fairly large amount of support by the government in terms of accommodation than men. Other kinds of accommodations like living temporarily with others, boarding houses, temporary lodgings etc. are mostly occupied by men rather than women.
						<br/>
						<br/> This picture overall shows that men are mostly affected by homelessness than women. It also shows that homeless women also receive a good amount of support by the government or by the organizations who provide accommodations. Therefore, significant steps must be taken to ensure that men and women are provided a fair amount of support by the government and the NGOs
					</p>
				</div>
